SUMMARY:Louisa's Garden Tour
DESCRIPTION:Get a close look at her IU diploma (one of the first awarded 
 to women in IU history)\, dresses and garments from the Elizabeth Sage Hi
 storic Costume Collection\, flowers chosen from her own writings to repre
 sent her life\, and discover what led her to be brave\, complex\, and sti
 ll cherished today. Louisa's Garden is a student-curated exhibition\, led
  by the Sarah L. Luckay fellow\, combining digital and physical exhibits 
 inside and outside the Wylie House Museum. Tours begin in the Morton C Br
 adley Jr. Education center and continue into both floors of the house Mus
 eum. Some parts of this tour will be outside and subject to weather. The 
 second floor of the museum is only accessible through stairs. &#160\;  To
 urs will be offered on Fridays and Saturdays through August 15\, excludin
 g June 19\, July 3\, and July 4.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Get a close look at her IU diploma (one
  of the first awarded to women in IU history)\, dresses and garments from
  the Elizabeth Sage Historic Costume Collection\, flowers chosen from her
  own writings to represent her life\, and discover what led her to be bra
 ve\, complex\, and still cherished today. Louisa's Garden is a student-cu
 rated exhibition\, led by the Sarah L. Luckay fellow\, combining digital 
 and physical exhibits inside and outside the Wylie House Museum. Tours be
 gin in the Morton C Bradley Jr. Education center and continue into both f
 loors of the house Museum. Some parts of this tour will be outside and su
 bject to weather. The second floor of the museum is only accessible throu
 gh stairs. &#160\;</p><p>  Tours will be offered on Fridays and Saturdays
  through August 15\, excluding June 19\, July 3\, and July 4.&#160\;</p>
